channel.title: My RAM
channel.description:
Well currently I have 1 gig of ram and I'm planning on buying another 1 hole gig.
At Bestbuy i searched my compatibility and it's DDR2 memory with support for DDR2 [b]PC2-4200[/b] speeds - 1 gig.
But I couldn't find it in the search. Can anyone tell me if they sell it there or any other local stores like WalMart or Target?
Thanks. I don't prefer buying it online because I'm to lazy to wait. Thanks =] My budget is like 35$.
[img]http://images.bestbuy.com/BestBuy_US/images/products/7997/7997475_sb.jpg[/img] That costs $35.00 but it's PNY - Optima 1GB [b]PC2-5300[/b] DDR2 DIMM Memory.
Oh and my p.c. is a HP.
http://www.bestbuy.com/site/olspage.jsp?skuId=7997475&st=RAM&type=product&id=1155071451493 Is the link.
Edit: I think this might work.
Here is what is ACP-EP MEMORY 1GB[b] PC2-4200 [b]DDR2[/b][/b] 533MHZ 240-PIN PC & mac DESKTOP Memory [b]DIMM[/b] - 1gig
[img]http://i.walmart.com/i/p/00/82/14/55/00/0082145500295_215X215.jpg[/img]
http://www.walmart.com/catalog/product.do?product_id=3609847
Is this compatible? I just don't get what the DIMM is?
My system requires to install memory in pairs.
